    <statement><div><p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Given a regular hexagon <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>, <m>C</m>, <m>D</m>, <m>E</m>, <m>F</m>, with <m>O</m> at the centre.</p>
<p>Let <m>\underline{a} = \vec{OA}</m> and <m>\underline{b}=\vec{OB}</m>.</p>
<figure class="HELM_figure">
<image alt="Regular hexagon centred at the origin with vertices starting at A, B, C, D, E and F." style="vertical-align:text-bottom; margin: 0 .5em;" class="img-responsive" width="50%" pi:generated="stack/images/stk-9-1-5-5-hexagon-adding-vectors-Poole-1.1-Ex14.png" xmlns:pi="http://pretextbook.org/2020/pretext/internal"/>
</figure>
<p>Express each of the following in terms of <m>\underline{a}</m> and <m>\underline{b}</m>.</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li><m>\vec{BC} = </m> <fillin characters="5" name="ans1"/>  </li>
<li><m>\vec{BC}+\vec{DE}+\vec{FA} = </m> <fillin characters="5" name="ans2"/>  </li>
<li><m>\vec{CF} = </m> <fillin characters="5" name="ans3"/>  </li>
</ol>
<p>Write <m>\underline{a}</m> and <m>\underline{b}</m> as <c>a</c> and <c>b</c>, respectively.</p></div></statement>
    <solution><ol class="HELM_parts">
<li>From the properties of the regular hexagon we know that <m> \vec{CB} </m> is parallel to <m> \underline{a} </m> and they have the same length. So, <m> \vec{BC} = -\underline{a} </m>.
</li>
<li>We notice that <m> \vec{CO} </m> is a translation of <m> \vec{DE} </m> and <m> \vec{OB} </m> is a translation of <m> \vec{FA} </m>. So, <m> \vec{BC} + \vec{DE} + \vec{FA} = \vec{BC} + \vec{CO} + \vec{OB} = 0 </m>.
</li>
<li>From the properties of the hexagon we know that the diagonal <m> \vec{CF} </m> is parallel to the side <m> \vec{BA} </m> and has twice it's length. So <m> \vec{CF} = 2 \vec{BA} = 2(\underline{a} - \underline{b}) </m>.
</li>
</ol></solution>
    <answer><p><m>-a</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>0</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>2 \left(a-b\right)</m></p></answer>
